# Legacy Analysis Safety

- Treat all LLM outputs as hypotheses until supported by code evidence.
- Never present inferred business behavior as guaranteed fact.
- Include explicit uncertainty labels when confidence is low or ambiguity exists.
- Prefer "unknown" over speculative conclusions when source evidence is incomplete.
- Surface parser/analysis gaps as part of results, not hidden implementation details.

## Required Output Behavior

- Every semantic claim must include source references (file, symbol, span).
- If evidence is missing, state "insufficient evidence" and block definitive wording.
- Distinguish direct extraction (from code) from inferred interpretation.
